Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?[DOSKUTSU]=20dos:=20Phase=209=20wave=2016.4=20p?=
 =?UTF-8?q?atch=200032=20=E2=80=94=20display-start=20scan-cap=20fix?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Wave 16.3 LFB sentinel (patch 0031) returned match=1 at all 5 sample
offsets (LFB+0/65535/65536/76799/131072) — writes round-trip cleanly
through the aperture into VRAM. Yet the bottom ~35 scanlines render
black on g2k Cirrus CL-GD5434 + UNIVBE 6.70. Conclusion: hypothesis
(b) confirmed — the display controller scan-caps at 64KB and never
reads bytes ≥65536 for display output, regardless of the configured
mode pitch / height.

This is now a DISPLAY-START register problem, not an LFB / banked /
aperture problem.

Two approaches, both env-gated by SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DISPLAY_START_FIX
(strict "1" match per CLAUDE.md DOSKUTSU env-var convention; default
OFF preserves current patch-0018 behaviour). Sequential — the
chip-direct display-start writes only fire if the VBE call failed.

Approach 1 — VBE 0x4F07 SET (during retrace) with BL=0x80, CX=DX=0.

  The pre-existing patch 0018 already calls 0x4F07 with BL=0x00
  (immediate SET) when use_lfb is true; the wave 16.3 capture saw
  that returning ax=0x004F (apparent success) yet bottom-strip-black
  persisted, suggesting the BIOS variant didn't actually commit the
  requested origin. BL=0x80 is the VBE 2.0+ variant explicitly
  waiting for the next vertical retrace before applying. Some
  Cirrus + UNIVBE BIOSes treat the two BL values differently —
  this is the cheap test before falling to chip-direct.

Approach 2 (display-start branch) — Cirrus chip-direct CRTC writes,
fired only when Approach 1 returned non-0x004F.

  CRTC at I/O 0x3D4 (index) / 0x3D5 (data). Display-start spread
  across:
    index 0x0C — display-start hi (bits 8-15)
    index 0x0D — display-start lo (bits 0-7)
    index 0x1A — bits 1-0 carry display-start bits 16-17 on 5434
                 ("Miscellaneous Control")
    index 0x1D — bit 7 carries display-start bit 18 on 5434
                 ("Display Start Address Extension")

  Zeroing 0x0C, 0x0D and bits 1-0 of 0x1A places the scan origin at
  byte 0 of the framebuffer. 0x1A is read-modified-written so other
  bits in that register are preserved.

Approach 2 (offset-register branch) — independent of display-start,
unconditional check.

  CRTC index 0x13 ("Offset Register") controls how many bytes the
  controller reads per scanline. For 320×240×8bpp packed the expected
  value is pitch/8 = 320/8 = 0x28. If the BIOS programmed something
  else (rare but possible on UNIVBE-rewritten BIOSes), the controller
  scans the wrong stride — symptom = horizontal repetition or shift.
  Always check this register and write the correct value if it
  mismatches.

Diagnostic logging — single token WAVE16-4-DISPLAY-START. Multiple
lines per modeset:
  - vbe_4F07 result (BX/CX/DX/AX values)
  - crtc_pre 5-register snapshot (0x0C 0x0D 0x13 0x1A 0x1D)
  - chip_direct displayStart_zero | displayStart_skipped
  - chip_direct offset_fix | offset_ok
  - crtc_post 5-register snapshot (verifies what stuck)

This lets us see exactly what the BIOS programmed during the mode
set vs what we wrote, and lets us correlate the visual outcome
against the register state that took effect.

Risks:

  1. Wrong register write → screen blanks / shows garbage. The hint
     is OFF by default so this only fires on opt-in. First iter is
     the test; visual fail = revert env, no rebuild needed.
  2. VBE 0x4F07 unsupported → AX != 0x004F triggers Approach 2's
     chip-direct path. Patch 0018's wave 16.3 logs already confirm
     0x4F07 IS supported on this BIOS, so Approach 1 is the
     expected primary path; Approach 2 is fallback only.
  3. CRTC index 0x1A bits we DON'T touch may carry chip-config state
     that should be preserved — using read-modify-write for 0x1A
     instead of full write to keep other bits intact.
  4. Reading uninitialised CRTC indices via inportb may return
     undefined values — we always set the index via outportb(0x3D4,
     idx) BEFORE inportb(0x3D5).
  5. 5434 extended index range is 0x18-0x1F per Cirrus 5434
     datasheet; 0x1D is in-range. Other Cirrus variants (5428, 5429,
     5446) may locate display-start bit 18 differently — if the chip
     isn't a 5434, the values are still logged but the user must
     verify the chip.

Predicted:

  - fps movement: 0 (display-controller fix, doesn't change CPU /
    bandwidth)
  - visual: bottom 35 scanlines render correctly + menu black-boxes
    around triangles resolve

Anchored at SDL_dosmodes.c line ~1145 (right after the patch 0018
display-start GET-SET-GET block, before the mouse min/max setup).
inportb / outportb are already used in this file (line 344, the
DAC pixel-mask probe) so the include chain is established.

Per docs/BOOT.md convention every new env var is documented in the
"Diagnostic / development options" subsection. The display-start fix
is dev-only for the wave 16.4 iter — promote to user-facing when
the fix is confirmed working.

Local-only patch per workspace policy. Never PR'd upstream.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c | 147 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 147 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
index 861470cb3..c734f8964 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
@@ -1143,6 +1143,153 @@ bool DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode(SDL_VideoDevice *device, SDL_VideoDisplay *sdl_displ
         }
     }
 
+    // DOSKUTSU patch 0032 (Phase 9 wave 16.4): display-start scan-cap fix.
+    // Wave 16.3 LFB sentinel (patch 0031) returned match=1 at all 5 sample
+    // offsets (LFB+0/65535/65536/76799/131072) — writes round-trip cleanly
+    // through the aperture into VRAM. Yet the bottom ~35 scanlines render
+    // black on g2k Cirrus + UNIVBE 6.70. Conclusion: hypothesis (b)
+    // confirmed — the display controller scan-caps at 64KB and never
+    // reads bytes ≥65536 for display output, regardless of pitch / height.
+    //
+    // Two approaches, both env-gated by SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DISPLAY_START_FIX
+    // (strict "1" match per CLAUDE.md DOSKUTSU env-var convention; default
+    // OFF preserves current patch-0018 behaviour). Sequential — Approach 2
+    // display-start writes only fire if Approach 1 failed.
+    //
+    //   Approach 1: VBE 0x4F07 SET DISPLAY START (during retrace) with
+    //     BL=0x80, CX=0, DX=0. The pre-existing patch 0018 already calls
+    //     0x4F07 with BL=0x00 (immediate SET) when use_lfb is true; in the
+    //     wave 16.3 capture this returned ax=0x004F (apparent success) yet
+    //     bottom-strip-black persisted, suggesting that BIOS variant didn't
+    //     actually commit the requested origin. BL=0x80 is the VBE 2.0+
+    //     variant explicitly waiting for the next vertical retrace before
+    //     applying. Some Cirrus + UNIVBE BIOSes treat the two BL values
+    //     differently — this is the cheap test.
+    //
+    //   Approach 2 (display-start): if Approach 1 returned non-0x004F,
+    //     fall back to chip-direct CRTC writes. The Cirrus CL-GD5434
+    //     uses VGA-compatible CRTC at I/O 0x3D4 (index) / 0x3D5 (data):
+    //       index 0x0C: display-start hi (bits 8-15)
+    //       index 0x0D: display-start lo (bits 0-7)
+    //       index 0x1A: extended bits — bits 1-0 carry display-start
+    //                   bits 16-17 (Cirrus 5434 "Miscellaneous Control")
+    //       index 0x1D: extended bit 7 carries display-start bit 18
+    //                   (Cirrus 5434 "Display Start Address Extension")
+    //     Zeroing 0x0C and 0x0D and bits 1-0 of 0x1A places the display
+    //     scan origin at byte 0 of the framebuffer regardless of what
+    //     the BIOS programmed during the mode set.
+    //
+    //   Approach 2 (offset-register) — independent of display-start.
+    //     CRTC index 0x13 ("Offset Register") controls how many bytes
+    //     the display controller reads per scanline. For a 320×240×8bpp
+    //     packed framebuffer the expected value is pitch/8 = 320/8 = 0x28.
+    //     If the BIOS programmed something else (rare but possible on
+    //     UNIVBE-rewritten BIOSes), the controller will scan the wrong
+    //     stride — symptom would be horizontal repetition / scrolling.
+    //     Always check this register and write the correct value if it
+    //     mismatches. The team-lead specifically called out this
+    //     possibility, separate from display-start.
+    //
+    // Diagnostic logging: WAVE16-4-DISPLAY-START token. Multiple lines:
+    //   - vbe_4F07 result
+    //   - crtc_pre values for 0x0C/0x0D/0x13/0x1A/0x1D
+    //   - chip_direct write log lines (when triggered)
+    //   - crtc_post values for verification
+    //
+    // Risks:
+    //   - Wrong register write → screen blanks or shows garbage. Hint is
+    //     OFF by default so this only fires when user opts in. First iter
+    //     IS the test.
+    //   - VBE 0x4F07 unsupported → AX != 0x004F triggers Approach 2.
+    //   - Read of unset CRTC index → set the index via outportb(0x3D4, ...)
+    //     BEFORE inportb(0x3D5). Done correctly here.
+    //   - 5434 extended index range is 0x18-0x1F per Cirrus 5434 datasheet;
+    //     0x1D is in-range. Other Cirrus variants (5428, 5429, 5446) may
+    //     locate display-start bit 18 differently — if the chip isn't a
+    //     5434, log the values but the user must verify the chip target.
+    //
+    // No fps movement expected — display-controller fix, not CPU/bandwidth.
+    // Visual win expected: bottom 35 scanlines render correctly + menu
+    // black-boxes around triangles resolve.
+    {
+        static int _ds_fix_enabled_cached = -1;
+        if (_ds_fix_enabled_cached == -1) {
+            const char *e = SDL_getenv("SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DISPLAY_START_FIX");
+            _ds_fix_enabled_cached = (e && e[0] == '1' && e[1] == 0) ? 1 : 0;
+        }
+        if (_ds_fix_enabled_cached) {
+            // ---- Approach 1: VBE 0x4F07 SET (during retrace), CX:DX = 0,0
+            __dpmi_regs ds_regs;
+            SDL_zero(ds_regs);
+            ds_regs.x.ax = 0x4F07;
+            ds_regs.x.bx = 0x0080; // BL=0x80 SET DISPLAY START during vertical retrace
+            ds_regs.x.cx = 0;      // X = 0 (first pixel of scanline)
+            ds_regs.x.dx = 0;      // Y = 0 (first scanline of frame)
+            __dpmi_int(0x10, &ds_regs);
+            const bool a1_ok = ((ds_regs.x.ax & 0x00FF) == 0x004F);
+            DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("WAVE16-4-DISPLAY-START: vbe_4F07 bx=0x0080 cx=0 dx=0 "
+                               "ax=0x%04X %s",
+                               ds_regs.x.ax, a1_ok ? "ok" : "FAIL");
+
+            // ---- Read pre-state of all relevant CRTC registers
+            outportb(0x3D4, 0x0C); const Uint8 pre_0C = inportb(0x3D5);
+            outportb(0x3D4, 0x0D); const Uint8 pre_0D = inportb(0x3D5);
+            outportb(0x3D4, 0x13); const Uint8 pre_13 = inportb(0x3D5);
+            outportb(0x3D4, 0x1A); const Uint8 pre_1A = inportb(0x3D5);
+            outportb(0x3D4, 0x1D); const Uint8 pre_1D = inportb(0x3D5);
+            DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("WAVE16-4-DISPLAY-START: crtc_pre 0x0C=0x%02X 0x0D=0x%02X "
+                               "0x13=0x%02X 0x1A=0x%02X 0x1D=0x%02X",
+                               pre_0C, pre_0D, pre_13, pre_1A, pre_1D);
+
+            // ---- Approach 2 (display-start branch): only if Approach 1 failed
+            if (!a1_ok) {
+                outportb(0x3D4, 0x0C);
+                outportb(0x3D5, 0x00);                            // hi byte = 0
+                outportb(0x3D4, 0x0D);
+                outportb(0x3D5, 0x00);                            // lo byte = 0
+                // 0x1A bits 1-0 = display-start bits 16-17 on 5434.
+                // Read-modify-write so other bits in this register are preserved.
+                outportb(0x3D4, 0x1A);
+                const Uint8 read_1A = inportb(0x3D5);
+                const Uint8 new_1A = (Uint8)(read_1A & ~0x03);
+                outportb(0x3D5, new_1A);
+                DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("WAVE16-4-DISPLAY-START: chip_direct displayStart_zero "
+                                   "wrote 0x0C=0x00 0x0D=0x00 0x1A=0x%02X (was=0x%02X)",
+                                   new_1A, read_1A);
+            } else {
+                DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("WAVE16-4-DISPLAY-START: chip_direct displayStart_skipped "
+                                   "(VBE 0x4F07 succeeded, no need for chip-direct)");
+            }
+
+            // ---- Approach 2 (offset-register branch): unconditional check
+            // Pitch/8 for 320×240×8bpp = 320/8 = 0x28. If the chip's offset
+            // register doesn't match, the controller is reading the wrong
+            // stride and the scan will repeat / shift horizontally.
+            const Uint8 expected_offset = (Uint8)(modedata->pitch / 8);
+            if (pre_13 != expected_offset) {
+                outportb(0x3D4, 0x13);
+                outportb(0x3D5, expected_offset);
+                DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("WAVE16-4-DISPLAY-START: chip_direct offset_fix "
+                                   "wrote 0x13=0x%02X (was=0x%02X expected=pitch/8=0x%02X)",
+                                   expected_offset, pre_13, expected_offset);
+            } else {
+                DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("WAVE16-4-DISPLAY-START: chip_direct offset_ok "
+                                   "0x13=0x%02X matches expected=pitch/8=0x%02X",
+                                   pre_13, expected_offset);
+            }
+
+            // ---- Read post-state of all CRTC registers for verification
+            outportb(0x3D4, 0x0C); const Uint8 post_0C = inportb(0x3D5);
+            outportb(0x3D4, 0x0D); const Uint8 post_0D = inportb(0x3D5);
+            outportb(0x3D4, 0x13); const Uint8 post_13 = inportb(0x3D5);
+            outportb(0x3D4, 0x1A); const Uint8 post_1A = inportb(0x3D5);
+            outportb(0x3D4, 0x1D); const Uint8 post_1D = inportb(0x3D5);
+            DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("WAVE16-4-DISPLAY-START: crtc_post 0x0C=0x%02X 0x0D=0x%02X "
+                               "0x13=0x%02X 0x1A=0x%02X 0x1D=0x%02X",
+                               post_0C, post_0D, post_13, post_1A, post_1D);
+        }
+    }
+
     if (SDL_GetMouse()->internal != NULL) { // internal != NULL) == int 33h services available.
         regs.x.ax = 0x7;                    // set mouse min/max horizontal position.
         regs.x.cx = 0;
-- 
